uired real external infra beyond local module wiring/database.","test_description":"Run integration test with fixed primary/fallback strings and known expected character edit distance, invoke quality tracker, then assert persisted metric value and associated translation record linkage in storage.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When both translators are available, the service returns the primary translation and logs the quality comparison in the background.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Candidate tests: Unit can check a selection helper prefers primary output, but misses orchestration failures across response path + async background logging trigger. Integration with both translator modules and background job/logging component catches real handoff/race/dispatch issues. Agentic rejected because assertions do not depend on model judgment quality, only precedence/orchestration. Workflow rejected: although multiple operations occur, they are not multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Create an integration test where primary and fallback both return deterministic strings; assert immediate response equals primary translation, then await/observe background task completion and verify quality-comparison log/metric record was written.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.24,"Integration":0.64,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
